line_1: Our Hair grows white, our Teeth grow black?
line_2: Or why, as Years our Frame attack,

line_1: Weel clad wi' coat o' glossy black;
line_2: His breast was white, his towzie back,

line_1: Lo! now with red rent cloak and bonnet black,
line_2: And torn green gown loose hanging at her back,

line_1: Tragedians all, and well-arranged in black!
line_2: Who nature, feeling, force, expression lack;

line_1: Yet we must reverence sacerdotal black,
line_2: And saddle all his faults on Nature's back.

line_1: Twa had manteeles o' dolefu' black,
line_2: The third, that gaed a wee a-back,

line_1: O'er a brown Cassock, which had once been black,
line_2: Which hung in tatters on his brawny back,

line_1: Contrary to the rest, was heben black,
line_2: On either side, and all adown her back,

line_1: Tho' the Coat's a good Coat, but alas it is black;
line_2: Not perfectly pleas'd with the Coat on his Back,

line_1: Those tresses, as the raven black,
line_2: That wav'd in ringlets down your back,

line_1: "A nasty man to make his face all black."
line_2: Next Neddy Nicely —" Fye, O fye, good lack,

line_1: That deeper sink to pitchy black,
line_2: On the deep shadows at their back
